  "body": "React 15.1.0\n\nGiven:\n\n``` js\nconsole.clear();\n\nclass Test1 extends React.Component {\n  componentDidMount() { console.log('mounted 1') }\n  componentWillUnmount() {\n    console.log('unmounted 1')\n    update2();\n  }\n  render() { return React.createElement('div', {}, 'test 1'); }\n}\n\nclass Test2 extends React.Component {\n  componentDidMount() { console.log('mounted 2') }\n  componentWillUnmount() { console.log('unmounted 2') }\n  render() { return React.createElement('div', {}, 'test 2'); }\n}\n\nconst render = (vNode) => {\n  ReactDOM.render(vNode, document.querySelector('#root'));\n};\n\nconst update1 = () => {\n  render(React.createElement(Test1, {}, []));\n}\n\nconst update2 = () => {\n  render(React.createElement(Test2, {}, []));\n}\n\nupdate1()\n\nsetTimeout(() => {\n  update2();\n}, 2000)\n\n```\n\nExpected console output:\n\n```\n\"mounted 1\"\n\"unmounted 1\"\n\"mounted 2\"\n```\n\nActual console output:\n\n```\n\"mounted 1\"\n\"unmounted 1\"\n\"mounted 2\"\n\"mounted 2\"\n```\n\nThe problem seems to be that I'm calling render from within `componentWillUnmount`â€”I suspect this is common i.e. dispatching Redux actions on unmount which trigger a synchronous render.\n",
